public class MessageList extends ObjectList<Message> implements MessageCounter
A list of messages that listens for and adds incoming messages. Only messages that are accepted by a Matcher (or Filter subclass) are added. The list of messages can be rebroadcast with Broadcaster.transmitAll(Iterable) and they can be counted with count(Message.Status) and count(Class). The method countWorseThanOrEqualTo(Message.Status) gives a count of all messages that are at least as bad or worse than the given message status value. For example, countWorseThanOrEqualTo(Status.PROBLEM). A filtered list of messages can be retrieved with matching(Matcher) and a StringList of formatted messages with formatted(). Statistics can be retrieved for types of messages and for message statuses with statisticsByType(Class[]) and statistics(Message.Status...), respectively.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
